==English==
{{wikipedia}}
===Etymology===
{{ME.}} [[weke]], [[wicke]]; {{OE.}} [[wēoce]]
===Noun===
'''wick'''
#something that [[transport]]s [[liquid]] by [[capillary action]], usually a [[woven]] [[string]], [[cord]], or [[strap]], usually of [[fabric]] or [[paper]]
#especially, on a [[candle]] or [[oil]] [[lamp]], the [[cord]] that delivers [[fuel]] into the [[flame]]
#:''Trim the '''wick''' fairly short, so that the flame does not smoke.''
#{{curling}} A shot where the played [[stone]] touches a [[stationary]] stone just enough that the played stone changes direction. 

===Transitive verb===
'''to wick'''
#to [[transmit]] liquid by capillary action
#:''The fabric '''wicks''' perspiration away from the body.''

